    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-03-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-03-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="538"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                <head>538. Telegram 2293 to New Delhi<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d538fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/3–1556. Confidential.
                        Drafted by Nagoski; cleared by Sebald and in substance by German (USINS),
                        Nelson (IES), and Withers (SOA). Repeated to Taipei for <persName
                            corresp="#p_RWS_1">Robertson</persName> as telegram Tosec 78 and to
                        Geneva for <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName> as telegram
                        1759.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1956-03-15">March 15, 1956, 3:43 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d538-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d538-1"/>
                <p>2293. Reference Secto 43 and memorandum given to Cooper for delivery to Nehru.
                    From 1949 to 1955, U.S. at public expense assisted 3641 Chinese to pursue
                    studies in U.S. and, among this group, provided travel funds to 771 who needed
                    money to return to mainland. Slightly over 80 percent of this travel assistance
                    was provided in 1949–50. Official totals on all Chinese definable as students
                    who have returned to mainland since 1949 not available.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HH_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
